</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9AD6543FFBBFFA2D1978800FF4AFBA4" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="910836C8FFBBFFA2D1978800FF4AFBA4" blockId="7.[151,1437,762,1149]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBBFFA2D1978800FAACFBEC" bold="true" box="[1167,1286,1051,1077]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species inhabits brackish tidal rivers and estuaries as well as freshwaters; lives in muddy burrows (
<bibRefCitation id="F5264B39FFBBFFA2D1D88824FF7EFBA4" author="Robertson, D. R. &amp; Allen, G. R." pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref66239" refString="Robertson, D. R. &amp; Allen, G. R. (2015) Shorefishes of the Tropical Eastern Pacific: online information system. Version 2.0. Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute, Balboa, Panama. Available from: https: // biogeodb. stri. si. edu / sftep / en / pages (accessed 27 August 2021)." type="url" year="2015">Robertson &amp; Allen 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
